Task: How do I rewrite paths in an AST&#39;s import tree?

 <p>I'm writing a program that will update a Rust project's imports to be from their new locations after a breaking change in a library. In this instance, I'd like to flatten all imports from <code>vexide::devices::item</code> to just <code>vexide::item</code>.</p>
<p>So far, I've tried using the <code>ra_ap_syntax</code> crate<sup>1</sup>, which has a data structure for representing Rust's <code>use</code> construct as tree of paths and sub-paths. For example, the following imports are parsed like this:</p>
<pre class="lang-rust prettyprint-override"><code>use vexide::{devices::smart::*, prelude::*};
